kde_entropy

{% raw %}

kde_entropy[source]

kde_entropy(data, sample_size=200, frac=1.0, progress_bar=False, **kde_kwargs)

Calculates the entropy of multiple continuous distributions. entropy equals np.mean(-np.log(p(x))) input should be of shape (n_distributions, n_sample_per_distribution, n_dims_in_distribtuion)

{% endraw %} {% raw %}
{% endraw %}

kde_entropy estimates a distribution of an aribtrary dimension random variable using kernel density estimation and calculates its entropy

quantile[source]

quantile(y_true, y_dists)

checks in which quantile lies y_true, given the predicted distribution y_true shape should be of shape (n_dists, n_samples ,n_dims) y_dists_should be of shape (n_dists, n_samples, n_dims)
